<div id="review_3146480794" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3146480794" />
    <a title="Michael || TheNeverendingTBR" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/93434926-michael-theneverendingtbr"><img alt="Michael || TheNeverendingTBR" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1644054285p2/93434926.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3146480794?book_show_action=true">Aug 08, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael || TheNeverendingTBR" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael || TheNeverendingTBR" href="/user/show/93434926-michael-theneverendingtbr">Michael || TheNeverendingTBR</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3146480794" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1900975029107382212">This book is about a infectious disease that causes people to burst into flames. There is no cure, and the only hope is to steer clear of the infected. Unless you&apos;re a mysterious man called The Fireman, who has somehow learned to control the fire and basically turned it into a superpower.<br/><br/>It was compared to The Stand but it&apos;s really nothing like it, it&apos;s just the same genre. <br/><br/>I enjoyed it but it slowed down in the middle considerably, it&apos;s like Joe Hill had a beginning and an ending set out and fi</span>
  <span id="freeText1900975029107382212" style="display:none">This book is about a infectious disease that causes people to burst into flames. There is no cure, and the only hope is to steer clear of the infected. Unless you're a mysterious man called The Fireman, who has somehow learned to control the fire and basically turned it into a superpower.<br /><br />It was compared to The Stand but it's really nothing like it, it's just the same genre. <br /><br />I enjoyed it but it slowed down in the middle considerably, it's like Joe Hill had a beginning and an ending set out and filled in the middle while writing; which is okay obviously but I felt like the story sort of dragged on in the middle and I found it hard to care about what was going on.<br /><br />I thought it read like a YA novel, I'm not saying that's bad or anything; I guess I went into it with high expectations due to The Stand comparison. <br /><br />I loved how there were a bunch of easter eggs throughout the book referring to either Joe Hill's other novels or Stephen King's novels.<br /><br />The ones I spotted <br />Christmasland (NOS4A2)<br />'Nick' character is deaf (The Stand)<br />Nozz-A-la (The Dark Tower)<br /><br /><br />I give it 3/5! 💫<br /><br />I think this would transfer well to the screen.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1900975029107382212" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


